
Errors - - 
The problem which cannot be resolved within the program
It is an illegal operation performed by the user
No error is thrown for input mismatch, and no error will be identified
Error occurs after the execution of the program
Errors can be occurred from system failures, hardware malfunctions and JVM

Exception - - 
The problem that can be resolved within the program
It is an legal operation performed by the user
An exception is an thrown for input mismatch which can be handled
Exception occurs during the execution of the program
There is no relation of exceptions with system failures and hardware malfunctions or JVM, it's purely depends on the code